# 4. Report Generation + Logging Workflow (MVP)

## 🎯 Objective

Create a **reliable, one-click report system** that:

* Captures **current device state (snapshot)**
* Runs **basic user-assisted diagnostics**
* Produces a **clear text report** (PDF optional later)
* Keeps **simple logs** of generated reports

Focus:

> Deterministic flow + clean data collection + readable output

---

# 🏗️ Module Architecture

```text
ReportActivity
   ├── Data Collector (System APIs)
   ├── Sensor Snapshot Collector
   ├── User Test Runner (guided)
   ├── Report Builder (formats text)
   └── Logger (in-memory / optional file)
```

---

# 🔄 End-to-End Workflow

```text
User clicks "Generate Report"
   ↓
Show "Preparing..." (loading)
   ↓
[1] Collect System Data
   ↓
[2] Capture Sensor Snapshot
   ↓
[3] Run Optional User Tests
   ↓
[4] Build Report Object
   ↓
[5] Render Report (TextView)
   ↓
[6] Save Log (optional)
```

---

# 📦 1. Data Model (Core)

```java
class DeviceReport {
    long timestamp;

    SystemInfo system;
    BatteryInfo battery;
    MemoryInfo memory;
    StorageInfo storage;
    NetworkInfo network;

    List<SensorSnapshot> sensors;
    List<TestResult> tests;

    String overallStatus;
}
```

---

## 🔹 Sub-Models

```java
class SensorSnapshot {
    String name;
    float[] values;
    String status;
}

class TestResult {
    String testName;
    boolean passed;
    String remark;
}
```

---

# 📊 2. System Data Collection

## 🔧 Collect Once (Snapshot)

```text
Battery → BatteryManager  
RAM → ActivityManager  
Storage → StatFs  
Network → ConnectivityManager  
```

---

## 🧠 Example Logic

```java
if (availRam > threshold)
    status = "Healthy";
else
    status = "Low Memory";
```

---

# 🎮 3. Sensor Snapshot Collection

## 🎯 Strategy:

* Capture **one-time value**, not continuous stream

---

## 🔧 Approach

```java
Sensor sensor = sm.getDefaultSensor(TYPE_ACCELEROMETER);
registerListener → wait for 1 update → unregister
```

---

## ⚠️ Timeout Handling

```text
If no data in 1–2 sec:
   → "No Data"
```

---

## 📌 Sensors to Include (MVP)

* Accelerometer
* Light
* Proximity
* Pressure (if available)
* Step Counter

---

# 🧪 4. User-Based Diagnostics (Guided Tests)

## 🎯 Purpose:

Test components not accessible via API

---

## 🔹 Test Flow UI

```text
Step 1: Screen Test
Step 2: Touch Test
Step 3: Audio Test
Step 4: Buttons Test
(Skip allowed)
```

---

## 🔹 Test Implementation

### Display Test

* Show color screens
* User confirms → pass/fail

---

### Touch Test

* Capture touch input
* If detected → pass

---

### Audio Test

* Record → playback
* User confirms

---

### Buttons Test

```java
onKeyDown(KEYCODE_VOLUME_UP)
onKeyDown(KEYCODE_VOLUME_DOWN)
```

---

# 🧠 Test Result Mapping

```java
if (userConfirmed)
    passed = true;
else
    passed = false;
```

